Interface JsonSerializer<B extends JsonModel>

  • Type Parameters:

    All Known Implementing Classes:
    ContributionSerializer, DefaultJsonSerializer, MessageSerializer, SubmissionSerializer

    public interface JsonSerializer<B extends JsonModel>
    This class provides a standard interface for turning a Jackson JsonNode into a JRAW JsonModel

                    java.lang.Class<T> clazz,
                    Model.Kind kind)
        Turns a JsonNode into a JsonModel
        Type Parameters:
        T - The type of object to return
        Parameters:
        node - The node to parse data from. This must be the root node of the object structure. In other words, it needs to have two children nodes: "kind" and "data".
        clazz - The class to make an instance of
        kind - The value of the class's Model.kind()
        Returns:
        A new JsonModel
